Ticket ID: SEC-DEV-2025-07-DESKTOPII
Title: Desktop II – UEFI BIOS Firmware Update and Platform Optimization
Classification: Firmware Lifecycle Management / Preventive Platform Hardening
Status: Closed – Hardened & Stable
Priority: High
Affected Asset: Desktop II (PC II – Custom Desktop Workstation)
Related Tickets: SYS-DEV-2026-02.08-DESKTOPII-SERVICING, SYS-DEV-2026-02.05-DESKTOPII-MAINT, SYS-DEV-2026-01.29-DESKTOPII-AUDIO, SEC-DEV-2025-09-DESKTOPII

Executive Summary
A controlled UEFI BIOS update was performed on Desktop II as part of preventive firmware lifecycle management and alignment with platform optimization protocols.
The update was executed manually using a USB-based flash through the motherboard’s native firmware utility to ensure procedural control and mitigate OS-level risks. System stability was verified prior to the update.
Objectives achieved:
	• Enhanced firmware integrity and platform reliability
	• Improved hardware compatibility
	• Enabled PCIe acceleration features (Above 4G Decoding, Resizable BAR)
	• Confirmed long-term system stability and peak performance
Post-update validation confirmed successful completion, full operational stability, and no regression.

Environment
	• Device: Desktop II (PC II)
	• Motherboard: ASUS ROG Maximus XII Hero
	• CPU: Intel Core i9-10900K
	• Firmware: ASUS UEFI BIOS
	• Memory: DDR4 – XMP II Profile (3600 MHz)
	• Storage: Multiple SSDs (GPT / UEFI configuration)
	• GPU Outputs: HDMI + DisplayPort connected during update
	• OS: Windows 11 Pro x64 (UEFI mode, Secure Boot capable)
	• Usage Profile: High-performance workstation / development / gaming
	• Location: Romania

Background
Firmware updates improve:
	• Hardware compatibility
	• CPU and memory stability
	• PCIe device interoperability
	• Security posture at firmware level
	• Support for modern acceleration features (Above 4G Decoding, Resizable BAR)
This update was initiated as preventive lifecycle maintenance and platform hardening following SEC-INC-2025-09-PSH-01. No malfunction was present at the time of execution.

Symptoms
	• No active instability
	• No POST errors
	• No firmware corruption
	• No OS boot issues

Business Impact
	• Impact Classification: Preventive / Risk-Controlled
	• Benefits Achieved:
• Maintains firmware lifecycle integrity
• Reduces risk of firmware-level vulnerabilities
• Ensures compatibility with current drivers and hardware
• Preserves peak CPU, memory, and PCIe performance
	• Risk Avoided:
• BIOS corruption
• Boot failure
• Firmware recovery procedures
• Extended downtime
	• No operational disruption occurred

Root Cause Analysis
	• No root cause; activity classified as proactive firmware lifecycle optimization and platform hardening

Initial Diagnostics
Pre-update checks confirmed:
	• Clean POST
	• Stable BIOS access
	• All SSDs detected
	• Stable GPU output
	• Stable power conditions
	• No OS instability
	• No pending Windows updates
	• No overclock instability
System baseline verified as healthy prior to flash.

Resolution Steps
Phase 1 – Firmware Preparation
	• Downloaded official BIOS from ASUS support
	• Verified motherboard compatibility and BIOS integrity
	• Validated file authenticity
Phase 2 – USB Flash Preparation
	• Prepared dedicated USB drive (FAT32)
	• Stored BIOS file exclusively on USB
Phase 3 – Safe Baseline Establishment
	• Entered UEFI BIOS
	• Reset BIOS to factory defaults
	• Cleared overclock and voltage customizations
	• Disabled custom memory profiles
Phase 4 – Firmware Flash Execution
	• Accessed ASUS BIOS update utility
	• Selected BIOS file from USB
	• Initiated flash process with uninterrupted power
	• Monitored completion; system auto-rebooted
Phase 5 – Post-Flash Configuration Restoration
	• Reconfigured BIOS manually:
• Trace Centering: Enabled
• Multicore Enhancements: Remove All Limits
• MCH Full Check: Enabled
• Above 4G Decoding: Enabled
• Resizable BAR: Enabled
	• Restored custom CPU, SSD, port, and memory settings (XMP II 3600 MHz)
Phase 6 – Boot & Stability Validation
	• Saved BIOS configuration
	• Successful POST and Windows boot
	• Multiple reboots validated stability

Resolved Conditions / Issues
	• BIOS updated to latest stable revision
	• Platform compatibility optimized
	• PCIe acceleration features enabled
	• BIOS integrity verified
	• No corruption detected

Final Outcome / Result
	• BIOS successfully updated
	• Custom performance profile restored
	• System fully operational
	• Peak stability confirmed
	• No regression detected

Post-Repair Validation
	• Clean POST
	• Stable OS boot
	• SSD detection normal
	• CPU and memory performance validated
	• GPU stable
	• No boot errors or firmware instability
	• Multiple reboot cycles confirmed sustained stability

Resolution and Preventive Recommendations
	• Use only official manufacturer BIOS versions
	• Reset BIOS to defaults before flashing
	• Perform manual USB-based flashing
	• Maintain stable power conditions
	• Never interrupt flash process
	• Document custom settings prior to modification
	• Validate full system stability post-update
	• Update firmware only when necessary and verified

Conclusion
Desktop II firmware lifecycle maintenance completed successfully under controlled conditions.
	• Platform integrity preserved
	• Performance maintained
	• Security posture strengthened
	• System status: Stable, Hardened, Operational
